(ESP32 Medicine Reminder Documentation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(README) Tj
T*
(------) Tj
T*
(# ESP32 Medicine Reminder Flutter App) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This Flutter app controls an ESP32 medicine reminder buzzer over HTTP while the ESP32 is running in Wi-Fi ) Tj
T*
(Access Point mode.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Base URL used by the app:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(`http://192.168.4.1`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Endpoints used:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- `GET /on`) Tj
T*
(- `GET /off`) Tj
T*
(- `GET /status`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Features) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- ON button to trigger medicine reminder) Tj
T*
(- OFF button to stop buzzer/reminder) Tj
T*
(- Live status refresh every 2 seconds) Tj
T*
(- Manual refresh button) Tj
T*
(- Connection error handling) Tj
T*
(- Works with ESP32 AP mode without internet) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Android Setup Fix) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Your Android SDK path should be:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(`C:\\Users\\kaasi\\AppData\\Local\\Android\\Sdk`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
